Investment Strategies – Comvest Partners




















Comvest Partners



















Investment Strategies


Our Private Equity and Direct Lending strategies provide tailored capital solutions to meet the needs of mature and growing middle-market companies.



Private Equity


Direct Lending











Private Equity – Comvest Investment Partners
Comvest’s Private Equity strategy pursues control investments in market leading companies that can benefit from our strategic and operational guidance to realize their full potential. Committed to the principles of partnership and collaboration, our investment professionals work closely with management to execute strategic initiatives focused on driving growth and operational improvement in the core business.



Investment Size

$35 million to $125 million investment per transaction
$75 million to $400 million of enterprise value
Flexibility to pursue larger transactions with LP co-investment



Financial Profile

Revenue between $50 million and $1 billion
Profitability is not a requirement
No minimum revenue for add-ons



Transaction Types

Corporate divestitures
Buyouts of institutional, family, or strategic ownership
Public-to-private transactions
Complex transactions and turnarounds
De novo growth, acquisition roll-ups, and industry consolidations



Target Industries

Business Services
Consumer & Retail
Healthcare Services
Industrials
Transportation & Logistics








Meet the Team





Select Investments





Case Studies












Direct Lending – Comvest Capital
Comvest’s Direct Lending strategy provides secured and unsecured debt to public and private companies, primarily in the lower middle market.  Using our operating resources, industry expertise and deep experience investing in the lower middle market, we are able to better understand our borrowers’ needs.  We apply this knowledge to create flexible financing structures tailored to meet the needs of growing companies. 



Investment Size

$10 million to $50 million hold size per transaction
Transaction size up to $100 million



Financial Profile

Revenue greater than $15 million
EBITDA greater than $3 million, with exceptions for high growth or specialty finance companies
Enterprise value greater than $20 million



Transaction Types

Senior Secured
Unitranche
First in Last Out (FILO) Facilities
Second Lien
Mezzanine
Equity Co-Investments



Investment Characteristics

Public or private ownership
Sponsored, non-traditionally sponsored, or non-sponsored
Investment supported by cash flow and enterprise value
Strong management team



Target Industries

Business and Financial Services
Education
Healthcare
Specialty Finance
Technology
Transportation








