ComVest Investment Partners IV, L.P.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 2:10 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of ComVest Investment Partners IV, L.P.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
ComVest Investment Partners IV, L.P. specializes in investments in management buyouts, turnarounds, mezzanine, Corporate Finance, restructurings, 363 bankruptcy auctions, recapitalizations, corporate orphans, industry consolidations, public-to-private transactions, investments in small public companies, distressed companies, lower middle market, and divestitures. The fund seeks to invest in software and information technology, healthcare, transportation, and financial technology services sectors. Within software and information technology, it invests in application software, information technology services and data storage, telephony device manufacturing, telephony service providers, and bus...
ComVest Investment Partners IV, L.P. specializes in investments in management buyouts, turnarounds, mezzanine, Corporate Finance, restructurings, 363 bankruptcy auctions, recapitalizations, corporate orphans, industry consolidations, public-to-private transactions, investments in small public companies, distressed companies, lower middle market, and divestitures. The fund seeks to invest in software and information technology, healthcare, transportation, and financial technology services sectors. Within software and information technology, it invests in application software, information technology services and data storage, telephony device manufacturing, telephony service providers, and business process outsourcing. Within the healthcare sector, the fund focuses on clinical research, medical technology and software, surgical devices, medical equipment manufacturing and service, and healthcare services. Within the transportation sector, it invests in airlines aviation services, aircraft sales and trading, trucking, logistics providers, distribution, warehousing, travel related services, and rail services. Within the financial technology services sector, the fund focuses on merchant processing, electronic invoice presentment and payment, check conversion/scanning, online banking finance, credit card authentication, and theft security. It seeks to invest between $10 million and $70 million per transaction in public or private companies with revenues between $15 million and $500 million and positive or negative EBITDA. The fund prefers to partner with management and makes control investments in public or private companies. The fund seeks to hold its investments for a period between three years and seven years.
Detailed Description


